======
RULES
======

(since there's no ClosedDoor in layers to prevent player-door conflict and door destruction, add a rule to stop at doors)

[ > Player | ClosedDoor no CrateInHole ] -> [ Player | ClosedDoor ]

(this is needed for dont_push_the_button and other levels too, pushes crate into open basement)
[ > Fighter | Crate | Background Basement ClosedDoor ] -> [ > Fighter | | Basement CrateInHole ClosedDoor ] sfx1

(paint water cross from waterseed for trapdoors)
[ WaterSeed ] -> [ Basement RayU RayD RayL RayR Water]
startloop
up    [ RayU | no Solid ] -> [ | RayU Basement ]
down  [ RayD | no Solid ] -> [ | RayD Basement ]
left  [ RayL | no Solid ] -> [ | RayL Basement ]
right [ RayR | no Solid ] -> [ | RayR Basement ]
endloop
late [ Rays ] -> []

[ MundaneSeed ] [ MirrorDL ] -> [ Mundane ] [ MirrorDL Mundane ]
[ MundaneSeed ] [ MirrorDR ] -> [ Mundane ] [ MirrorDR Mundane ]
[ MundaneSeed ] -> [ ]

(paint neighbour undertiles into mirror background, for worlds_collide)
[ MirrorBackground | HeroBackground | Hole ] -> [ MirrorBackground | MirrorBackground | Hole ]

(Island border)

(
left  [ Mirror ] [ WaterHere no AddLandL | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ WaterHere AddLandLUD | ]
right [ Mirror ] [ WaterHere no AddLandR | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ WaterHere AddLandRUD | ]

up    [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLUD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLD | WaterHere ]
up    [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRUD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRD | WaterHere ]

down  [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLUD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLU | WaterHere ]
down  [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRUD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRU | WaterHere ]

down  [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ | WaterHere ]
down  [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ | WaterHere ]

left  [ Mirror ] [ no WaterHere no RemoveLandL | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLUD | WaterHere ]
right [ Mirror ] [ no WaterHere no RemoveLandR | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRUD | WaterHere ]

up    [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLUD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLD | ]
up    [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRUD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRD | ]

down  [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLUD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLU | ]
down  [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRUD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRU | ]

down  [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ | ]
down  [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ | ]
)


( make all possible copies )
[ action Player ] [ MirrorGuy HasReflection ] [ MirrorGuyReflection ] -> [ action Player ] [ MirrorGuy HasReflection ] [ MirrorGuyReflection MirrorGuy ] sfx5
[ action Player ] [ SMirrorGuy HasReflection ] [ MirrorGuyReflection ] -> [ action Player ] [ SMirrorGuy HasReflection ] [ MirrorGuyReflection SMirrorGuy ] sfx5
[ action Player ] [ ReflectableCrate HasReflection ] [ CrateReflection ] -> [ action Player ] [ ReflectableCrate HasReflection ] [ CrateReflection ReflectableCrate ] sfx5
[ action Player ] [ Goblin HasReflection ] [ GoblinReflection ] -> [ action Player ] [ Goblin HasReflection ] [ GoblinReflection Goblin ] sfx5

([ action Player ] [ Reflectable HasReflection ] [ Reflection ] -> [ action Player ] [ Reflectable HasReflection ] [ Reflection Reflectable ] sfx5) ( breaks proper copying )

( kill the original )
[ action Player ] [ Reflectable HasReflection ] -> [ action Player ] [ ]


[ CharacterSwap MirrorGuy ] [ SWizard ] -> [ SMirrorGuy] [ Wizard ] sfx1
[ CharacterSwap MirrorGuy ] [ SMirrorGuy] -> [ SMirrorGuy] [ MirrorGuy ] 
[ CharacterSwap Wizard ] [ SMirrorGuy ] -> [ SWizard ] [ MirrorGuy ] sfx1


(Clear state)

[ LOS ] -> []
[ HasReflection ] -> []
[ Reflection ] -> []
[ CrateReflection ] -> []

[ action MirrorGuy ] -> [ MirrorGuy ]

[ moving MirrorGuy ] -> [ moving MirrorGuy HasReflection ] (testing killing)


[ Hole Vulnerable ] -> [ Hole Vulnerable Dying ]


(Push things)

[ > MirrorGuy | Hole ] -> [ MirrorGuy | Hole ] sfx4

[ >  MirrorGuy | MirrorCrate | no Solid ] -> [  >  MirrorGuy | > MirrorCrate | ] sfx1
[ >  MirrorGuy | Mirror | no Solid ] -> [  >  MirrorGuy | > Mirror | ] sfx1 (allow pushing mirror into the hole)

[ > MirrorGuy | MirrorInHole ] -> [ MirrorGuy | MirrorInHole ] (stop mirrorguy from stepping on mirror in hole)

[ > MirrorGuy | stationary Mirror | Hole ] -> [ MirrorGuy | Mirror | Hole ] sfx4

[ >  MirrorGuy | MirrorCrate | > MirrorGuy ] -> [  >  MirrorGuy | > MirrorCrate | > MirrorGuy ] sfx1
[ >  MirrorGuy | Mirror | > MirrorGuy ] -> [  >  MirrorGuy | > Mirror | > MirrorGuy ] sfx1

([ > Mirror | Hole ] -> [ Mirror | Hole ] sfx4)

[ > Pushable | no Solid ] -> [ | Pushable ]
+ [ > MirrorGuy | no Solid ] -> [ | MirrorGuy ] sfx0

[ > MirrorGuy ] -> [ MirrorGuy ] sfx4

[ MirrorGuy Hole ] -> [ Hole ]

([ Mirror Hole ] -> cancel)


[ NormalCrate Hole ] -> [ CrateInHole ] sfx3
[ ReflectableCrate Hole ] -> [ CrateInHole ] sfx3
[ Mirror Hole ] -> [ MirrorInHole ] sfx3

[ MirrorGuy ] [ HasReflection ] -> [ MirrorGuy ] []

[ HasReflection ] -> cancel (all MirrorGuys dead)


(hero rules)

([Saved] [Goal] -> [] [HasSavedDoor]) (Remembering whether we saved someone last round by temporarily changing some door to a HasSavedDoor. This is purely for sound effects purposes.)
(the rule above apparently breaks the compound goal+monsterdoor things in mosh_pit_small, so I commented it out)

[Corpse] -> Restart

[ >  Fighter | Moveable ] -> [  >  Fighter | > Moveable  ]

[ > Moveable | Moveable ] [ Fighter] -> [ > Moveable | > Moveable ] [ Fighter] (Fighters push.)


[ < Thief | Moveable ] -> [ < Thief | < Moveable ] (Thieves pull.)

[ > Wizard ] -> [ Wizard > Warpball]

(basement door rule added. check carefully. should work both with heroes1_21_v3 and dunk_tank_alt)

[ > Warpball | ClosedDoor Basement ] -> [ | ClosedDoor Basement > Warpball ]
+ [ > Warpball | no Moveable no Static ] -> [ | > Warpball ]

(continue wizard rules as usual)

[ > Warpball | Static] [Wizard] -> [ | Static ] [> Wizard]
[ > Warpball | Moveable ] [Wizard] -> [ | Wizard ] [Moveable] sfx0
[ > Warpball] [Wizard] -> [] [> Wizard]
(Wizards telexport. What they really do is shoot a "warpball", which causes them to move normally if it hits a wall or the edge of the screen and warp if it hits something they can warp with.)

(Druid does his thing. Warpball gets reused as a placeholder here. That's gonna happen a lot.)

[> Druid | Bush] -> [Druid | Crate ] sfx8
[> Druid | Crate] -> [Druid | Bush ] sfx8

[> Druid | Goblin] -> [Druid | FrozenGoblin ] sfx8
[> Druid | DragonUp] -> [Druid | FrozenDragonUp ] sfx8
[> Druid | DragonDown] -> [Druid | FrozenDragonDown ] sfx8
[> Druid | DragonLeft] -> [Druid | FrozenDragonLeft ] sfx8
[> Druid | DragonRight] -> [Druid | FrozenDragonRight ] sfx8

[> Druid | FrozenGoblin] -> [Druid | Goblin ] sfx8
[> Druid | FrozenDragonUp] -> [Druid | DragonUp ] sfx8
[> Druid | FrozenDragonDown] -> [Druid | DragonDown ] sfx8
[> Druid | FrozenDragonLeft] -> [Druid | DragonLeft ] sfx8
[> Druid | FrozenDragonRight] -> [Druid | DragonRight ] sfx8

[> Druid | Healer] -> [Druid | Healer Saved]
[> Druid | Hero] -> [Druid | Hero Warpball]
[Warpball | Healer] -> [Saved | Healer]
[Warpball Hero] -> [Wall] sfx8
(What strategic purpose could it serve for healers to protect against petrification? None, but it's fun.)

(I mean, theoretically you could write some horrid dragon breath timing puzzle where the ability to delay an extra turn without moving or switching characters is necessary in order to let you move someone else at the correct moment, but even if dragons still existed, that sounds like a really gross level.)

(Bard moves stuff. Reusing "WarpBall" for totally different purpose, so we can cancel the move if he doesn't move.)

(
[> Bard no Note] -> [> Note > Bard WarpBall]
[> Note] [Note] -> [> Note] [> Note]
[> Note BardMoveable | no Static no BardMoveable no Bard] -> [| BardMoveable Sfx7]
+[> Note Bard WarpBall| no Static no BardMoveable no Bard] -> [| Bard]
)

[> Bard] -> [> Note > Bard WarpBall]
